Italian Foreign Minister to visit Moscow on Wednesday 
Italian Foreign Affairs Minister Susanna Agnelli is due to meet Russian
counterpart Andrei Kozyrev here on Wednesday, a Foreign Affairs
Ministry spokesman said Tuesday quoted by the news agency Interfax.
The ministers will discuss Russo-Italian relations, European security
issues as well as the conflict in ex-Yugoslavia.
Relations between Moscow and the European Union and NATO will also be
thrashed out. Agnelli is also scheduled to meet Russian Deputy Prime
Minister Anatoly Chubais.
Spanish Premier Felipe Gonzales and Jacques Santer, President of the
European Commission, are also expected here Wednesday for a two day
visit.
